net.sourceforge.waters.model.base

Class AbstractEqualityVisitor

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sourceforge.waters.model.base.AbstractEqualityVisitor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ProxyVisitor
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ModuleEqualityVisitor, ProductDESEqualityVisitor

    public abstract class AbstractEqualityVisitor
extends Object
implements ProxyVisitor

    A visitor to compare Proxy objects for content-based equality.

    All Proxy objects implement default object equality. The AbstractEqualityVisitor provides for content-based equality. It can be configured to respect or not to respect geometry information found in some Proxy objects.

    In addition, the AbstractEqualityVisitor can optionally produce detailed diagnostic information when two items are found to be not equal. This is useful for testing and debugging, but it does have an impact on performance.

    Author:
    Robi Malik

    • Constructor Detail

      • AbstractEqualityVisitor

        public AbstractEqualityVisitor(boolean diag,
                               boolean geo)
        Creates a new equality checker.
        Parameters:
        diag - A flag, indicating whether the equality checker should provide diagnostic information if items compared are found not to be equal. Diagnostic information can be retrieved using getDiagnostics(). This is useful for testing and debugging, but it does have an impact on performance.
        geo - A flag, indicating whether the equality checker should consider geometry information. If true objects will be considered equal if their contents and geometry are equal, otherwise any geometry information will be ignored when checking for equality.
